% --- setpagedevice (last: it replaces the device) ---
<< /OutputDevice /pgm /PageSize [50 25] /HWResolution [144 144] /TextAlphaBits 3 >> setpagedevice
DEVICE /dimensions get dup 0 get 100 eq exch 1 get 50 eq and
    (setpagedevice sizes the device from PageSize and HWResolution) assert
DEVICE /TextAlphaBits get 3 eq (device features land on the device) assert
currentpagedevice /HWResolution get 0 get 144 eq (currentpagedevice reports the request) assert
1 0 dtransform pop 2 sub abs 0.01 lt (the device matrix carries the resolution) assert
<< /PageSize [25 25] >> setpagedevice
DEVICE /dimensions get 0 get 50 eq (a partial request merges over the previous one) assert
DEVICE /TextAlphaBits get 3 eq (merged features persist) assert
<< /OutputDevice /null /PageSize [10 10] >> setpagedevice
currentpagedevice /TextAlphaBits known not
    (switching OutputDevice discards the accumulated parameters) assert
currentpagedevice /HWResolution known not
    (a device switch reverts unstated parameters to defaults) assert

